      "_id": "6a527120bcfd15e71cdf5826",
      "title": "The Architecture of Lightning-Fast Animations",
      "slug": "architecture-lightning-fast-animations",
      "content": "## 1. Frame rate preservation in modern browsers\nPreserving a constant 60fps (or 120fps on modern screens) is critical to maintaining a luxury feeling. Dropped frames disrupt the visual flow. We achieve this by moving heavy rendering tasks off the main thread:\n- Use hardware-accelerated CSS transforms (`translate3d`, `scale`).\n- Minimize paint invalidation zones.\n- Leverage GPU compositing.\n\n## 2. Dynamic easing equations\nLuxury interfaces rely on custom cubic-bezier curves rather than default ease-in or ease-out timings. The transition timing must feel deliberate:\n- **Cubic Bezier (0.16, 1, 0.3, 1):** Highly recommended for fluid, premium slide-outs.\n- **Spring Physics:** Used dynamically in Framer Motion to preserve natural inertia.",
      "image": "data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mNkYAAAAAYAAjCB0C8AAAAASUVORK5CYII=",
      "tags": [
        "Animations",
        "CSS",
        "Performance"
      ],
      "readTime": "4 min read",
      "published": true,
      "order": 1,
      "__v": 0
    },
    {
      "_id": "6a527120bcfd15e71cdf5827",
      "title": "Zero Latency: Optimizing Next.js for Monaco and Beyond",
      "slug": "zero-latency-optimizing-nextjs-monaco",
      "content": "## 1. Static site pre-generation\nBy pre-building all our routes to static HTML on the server side, browser load times are reduced to standard CDNs edge speeds. Pages serve in under 100 milliseconds, globally.\n\n## 2. In-memory data caches\nWe route database queries into a local file-based cache to bypass Atlas latency on dynamic requests. When database changes occur, the admin API triggers an on-demand revalidation.",
      "image": "data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAYAAAAfFcSJAAAADUlEQVR42mP8z8BQDwAEhQGAhKmMIQAAAABJRU5ErkJggg==",
      "tags": [
